    // Since OR_val is the OR of all elements, if a bit is set in OR_val, it must be set in at least one element.
    // If OR_val = nums[k], it means all bits set in all elements nums[i]...nums[j] must only be set in nums[k].
    // This implies that for all elements nums[l] in the subarray, nums[l] | nums[k] = nums[k].
    // In other words, every element in the subarray must be a "submask" of nums[k].
    // nums[l] | nums[k] = nums[k]  <=>  nums[l] is a subset of bits of nums[k].

